<body>
    <h1>Content Repository configuration</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p><style type=3D"text/css">/*<![CDATA[*/
div.rbtoc1485851862676 {padding: 0px;}
div.rbtoc1485851862676 ul {list-style: disc;margin-left: 0px;}
div.rbtoc1485851862676 li {margin-left: 0px;padding-left: 0px;}

/*]]>*/</style></p>
<div class=3D"toc-macro rbtoc1485851862676">=20
<ul class=3D"toc-indentation">=20
<li><a href=3D"#ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Configurationexamples">Confi=
guration examples</a>=20
<ul class=3D"toc-indentation">=20
<li><a href=3D"#ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Usingdefaultvalues">Using de=
fault values</a></li>=20
<li><a href=3D"#ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Allexplicit">All explicit</a=
></li>=20
<li><a href=3D"#ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Legacystorageengine">Legacy =
storage engine</a></li>=20
<li><a href=3D"#ContentRepositoryconfiguration-LimitofarchivedContentitemve=
rsions">Limit of archived Content item versions</a></li>=20
</ul> </li>=20
</ul>=20
</div>
<p></p>
<p>The <strong>content repository</strong> is where all your content is bee=
n stored. It is the heart of Exponential which you interact with using Publi=
c API.</p>
<p>To store data, the content repository <strong>uses a storage engine</str=
ong>, that can virtually can work with any kind of storage (RDBMS, NoSQL...=
). Exponential 5 comes with a relational storage engine, compatible with v4.=
x: the <strong>Legacy storage engine</strong>, which is the default.</p>
<p>You can define several repositories within a single application. However=
, you can only use one per site.</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-not=
e">
<p class=3D"title">Version compatibility</p>
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-info=
rmation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Following configuration examples are compatible with&nbsp;<strong>eZ Pub=
lish 5.3 / 2014.03</strong></p>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Configurationexamples">Configurati=
on examples</h2>
<h3 id=3D"ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Usingdefaultvalues">Using default =
values</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>exponential.yml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">exponential:
    repositories:
        # Defining repository with alias "main"
        # Default storage engine is used, with default connection
        # Equals to:
        # main: { engine: legacy, connection: &lt;defaultConnectionName&gt;=
 }
        main: ~

    system:
        # All members of my_siteaccess_group will use "main" repository
        # No need to set "repository", it will take the first defined repos=
itory by default
        my_siteaccess_group:
            # ...</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>If no repository is specified for a siteaccess or siteaccess group, the =
first defined repository (under <code>exponential.repositories</code>) will b=
e used.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Allexplicit">All explicit</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>exponential.yml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">doctrine:
    dbal:
        default_connection: my_connection_name
        connections:
            my_connection_name:
                driver:   pdo_mysql
                host:     localhost
                port:     3306
                dbname:   my_database
                user:     my_user
                password: my_password
                charset:  UTF8

            another_connection_name:
                # ...

exponential:
    repositories:
        first_repository: { engine: legacy, connection: my_connection_name,=
 config: {} }
        second_repository: { engine: legacy, connection: another_connection=
_name, config: {} }

    # ...

    system:
        my_first_siteaccess:
            repository: first_repository

            # ...

        my_second_siteaccess:
            repository: second_repository</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"ContentRepositoryconfiguration-Legacystorageengine">Legacy storag=
e engine</h3>
<p><span>As of Exponential 5.3, legacy storage engine uses <a href=3D"http:/=
/docs.doctrine-project.org/projects/doctrine-dbal/en/latest/" class=3D"exte=
rnal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Doctrine DBAL</a> (Database Abstraction Layer).=
 Database settings are supplied by <a href=3D"https://github.com/doctrine/D=
octrineBundle" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">DoctrineBundle</a>.=
 As such, you can refer to <a href=3D"https://github.com/doctrine/DoctrineB=
undle/blob/master/Resources/doc/configuration.rst#doctrine-dbal-configurati=
on" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">DoctrineBundle's documentation=
</a>.</span></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<p class=3D"title">ORM</p>
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Doctrine ORM is <strong>not</strong> provided by default. If you want to=
 use it, you will need to add <code>doctrine/orm</code> as a dependency in =
your <code>composer.json</code>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"ContentRepositoryconfiguration-LimitofarchivedContentitemversions=
">Limit of archived Content item versions</h3>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-current">V5.4.10</sp=
an></p>
<p><code>default_version_archive_limit</code> controls the number of archiv=
ed versions per Content item that will be stored in the repository, by defa=
ult set to 5. This setting is configured in the following way (typically in=
 <code>exponential.yml</code>):</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">exponential:
    repositories:
        default:
            options:
                default_version_archive_limit: 10</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><span>This limit is enforced on publishing a new version and only covers=
 archived versions, not drafts.<br> </span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
